<font color="#FF0000">A SPECIAL PLACE</font><br>
<tt>Wed Jul 30  1:37:31 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
The sparring is fun... the humor is great.  There is a far left and a far right and a strong middle.<br>
Is there a possibility of a thread where suffering people can talk about Isolation, memory loss, sleep disturbances, intrusive thoughts, exagerated startle response, fight or flight mechanisms and their impact on the endocrine system, sensation seeking, anger and emotion control, triggering stimuli, depression, suicide ideation, sadness/remorse, contempt for authority and trust issues and any number of other subjects that combat veterans have to deal with on a daily basis.  If so, how do we do it... and remain fair to all who want to post.  Could we make an agreement to ban extreme profanity?  Can we dictate guidelines without curbing sincere emotion and thought?  How about no name calling, even in jest?  Can we talk about how bad the war was for us on a personal level and leave whether I should or should not have gone out of it?  Would that compromise the validity of the discussion?  Could we ask questions of one another and not lecture each other?  Would we be able to get someone gently back on track if there was an infraction?  People are watching and reading who need help, want answers, seek enlightment, and want to give or borrow... to and from all of us.  Is there a way to let us and others vent profound political and religious points at a different thread? Perhaps we could start a thread on just discussing the possibilities... agree to do it or not do it... propose, select and reject rules...?<br>
You have the right to get drunk but not at the day care center.  You have the right to swim naked but not at the public swimming pool... etc.  No caustic comments, just different perspective... constructive advice... etc.
<p><code>-- eramon@edumaster.net  (Edward Ramon) </code><p>


